=== BT-545 Round 1 attack -- Lefschetz + diamond symmetry + Kahler id ===

--- PHASE A: Hodge diamond symmetry audit ---
[P2] dim_C=2, symmetry audit
  (p,q)<->(q,p) conjugation: OK
  Serre duality (n-p,n-q): OK
[P1xP1] dim_C=2, symmetry audit
  (p,q)<->(q,p) conjugation: OK
  Serre duality (n-p,n-q): OK
[Q5] dim_C=3, symmetry audit
  (p,q)<->(q,p) conjugation: OK
  Serre duality (n-p,n-q): OK
[Enr] dim_C=2, symmetry audit
  (p,q)<->(q,p) conjugation: OK
  Serre duality (n-p,n-q): OK

--- PHASE B: chi from alternating Hodge sum (topological cross-check) ---
  chi(P^2)       = 3   (expected 3)
  chi(P^1xP^1)   = 4   (expected 4)
  chi(Q_5)       = -200   (expected -200, CY3)
  chi(Enriques)  = 12   (expected 12)
  chi-topology agreement: 4/4

--- PHASE C: Lefschetz (1,1) theorem (K=1 Hodge conjecture) ---
[Lefschetz-(1,1) P2]
  NS rank rho(X)     = 1
  h^{1,1}(X)         = 1
  rho = h^{1,1} ? YES  (Lefschetz (1,1) verified: K=1 Hodge conj)
[Lefschetz-(1,1) P1xP1]
  NS rank rho(X)     = 2
  h^{1,1}(X)         = 2
  rho = h^{1,1} ? YES  (Lefschetz (1,1) verified: K=1 Hodge conj)
[Lefschetz-(1,1) Enr]
  NS rank rho(X)     = 10
  h^{1,1}(X)         = 10
  rho = h^{1,1} ? YES  (Lefschetz (1,1) verified: K=1 Hodge conj)
  Lefschetz (1,1) holds on 3/3 test cases

--- PHASE D: Kahler identity Delta_d = 2 Delta_dbar on T^2 ---
[Kahler identity  Delta_d = 2 Delta_dbar  on T^2 scalars]
  checked 48 modes, all satisfy lam_d / lam_dbar = 2
  Kahler identity  Delta_d = 2 Delta_dbar  verified numerically.

--- PHASE E: h^{1,1}(P^n) = 1 for all n (trivial Picard) ---
  h^{1,1}(P^1 .. P^10) all = 1, rho=1 by Lefschetz: cycle-theoretic consistent

--- SUMMARY ---
  A) diamond symmetry              : 4/4 varieties clean
  B) chi topological cross-check   : 4/4 match
  C) Lefschetz (1,1) verified      : 3/3 surfaces
  D) Kahler identity Delta_d=2dbar : true
  E) h^{1,1}(P^n)=1 consistent     : true

honest verdict:
  All numerics consistent with known Hodge theory literature.
  K=1 Hodge conjecture (Lefschetz (1,1)) confirmed on small surfaces.
  K>=2 cases NOT touched -- Hodge conjecture remains OPEN for
  generic abelian 4-folds, generic projective varieties in dim >= 4.
  Round 1 did NOT produce new law/proof. MISS expected.

